705610f-a.title: Brooklyn: Maspeth Avenue - Morgan Avenue
705610f-a.text:
Maspeth Ave., at the N.E. corner of Morgan Ave., showing a frame struct-
ure, said to have been built from timber of the old Manor Bouse. This
home was used by workmen of Peter Cooper the glue manufacturer.
March 1909.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

705609f-a.title: Brooklyn: Maspeth Avenue - Morgan Avenue
705609f-a.text:
Maspeth Ave., at the N.W. corner of Morgan Ave. The houses at the
right face on Maspeth Ave. Morgan Ave. is distinguishable by the
electric line pole thereon. The view is southward.
i23.
